user.biography:
🏅 2018 CCPS Teacher of the Year (MD)
🏳️‍🌈 Proud 🔆
✨ Author of @keepingthewonder
😎 Click below for resources!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Staci Lamb | English Teacher on August 14, 2021 tagging @appleridgefarmva. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text: Guess where I stayed? On a farm, of course, but in a caboose! 🚂 This farm has cabooses you can stay in, and the proceeds help fund local youth group activities! What a cool way to spend my last few days before school. Also, I'm on the road again heading somewhere really special and a place I think you might recognize 🧐 Any guesses? 🙂

node.text: This classroom is for everyone ✨ Lauren (@classroomyogi) literally radiates positivity on here, and every month, she picks a different LGBTQIA+ organization to donate to. If you need some new stickers, shirts, sweatshirts, etc., be sure to click the link in @classroomyogi 's bio 💛 15% of the profits will be donated 🙂

node.text:
Every year, I use some of the same strategies, but I always try to incorporate a twist or approach it differently. These activities and organizational tools are ones I use time and time again without fail. 🙌 I'm excited to incorporate them in just a few weeks!⁣
⁣
All of these and more are on sale in my TPT store, and you can use code BTS2021 to save up to 25%! Link in bio 💛⁣
⁣
What's your go-to idea every year?

node.text:
Me realizing it's August: 😳😳😳⁣
⁣
I hung out with some cows last week and obviously had to take pictures with them. 🐂⁣
⁣
BTW, if you're free later tonight, we're doing a Twitter chat to share some ideas as we head back into school mode. Just search #tlap and join the chat for some inspiration ✨

#ilovecows #cowsarecute #iwouldliketoownacow #unfortunatelyiliveinatownhouse #maybetheneighborswontnotice

node.text:
Wonder Box Giveaway time ✨ ⁣
⁣
Want all these ~wonderful~ items to complement your book PLUS a few surprise items?⁣
⁣
We only have a few days left to get the Wonder Welcome kit with free resources, so let me know with an emoji where you fall:⁣
⁣
⏳ Planning to get the book by 7/31!⁣
📘 Already received your copy of @keepingthewonder book!⁣
✅ Submitted the Google Form to get your free resources!⁣
🎁 Received your free resources!⁣
✨ Already thinking of ways to use your free resources!⁣
⁣
Giveaway ends Friday 7/30 at midnight. Must be 18+. Not sponsored by IG.

node.text: The idea started 3 years ago, and from there, we took all these steps into creating what is now the @keepingthewonder book. 💜✨ The book is ON SALE right now, but we don't know for how long, so if you haven't snagged your copy, go now!! Link in bio 🥰 And don't forget to head to our website after to get your free Wonder Welcome kit!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Staci Lamb | English Teacher on July 22, 2021 tagging @keepingthewonder. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: Cow-approved! 🐂 This sweet girl couldn't wait to read (and by read, I mean try to lick) the @keepingthewonder book, so I decided to compromise and let her take a picture with it 🤷‍♀️ I'm not an expert at cow language, but I'm pretty sure she mooed that it's a good book and the perfect way to recharge and reignite your ~wonderful~ teaching as we head back into the school year! 🥰 Don't forget: all books purchased through 7/31 get free wonder-themed resources! 💜 Link in bio!

It's here!!! ✨🙌 I hope you can see the absolute joy on my face holding our book. Like an actual BOOK! 🥰 
 
You can get your copy in just 2 days if you order today!!! 🙂 The link to grab your copy is in my bio 💛 
 
If you buy before 7/31, you'll get a special Wonder Welcome gift with free resources and an extra special surprise (it's personally my favorite piece ✨). 
 
Thank you, thank you, thank you for all the love and support 💜

node.text: Over the last few weeks, I've been anticipating the release of our @keepingthewonder book, but I knew seeing this page would be the hardest part. Before my mom passed, I was able to show her the PDF of our book. The cover. The interior illustrations. How the little three stars next to my name magically and coincidentally match my tattoo. ✨ And, just like she always did, she told me how proud she was of me. This has been 2+ years in the making, and as of tomorrow, I can officially say, "I'm an author!" I don't know what the next  chapter of my life entails (except maybe owning some cows), but I know she'll be proud 💜 Thank you all for giving me this space, this little teacher IG community, allowing me to meet my @keepingthewonder friends. It has been truly life-changing. 💖

node.text:
It's Throwback Thursday, right? 🙂 The second picture was my classroom back in 2017-2018. Although I love my classroom now, I also loved the simplicity of that theme. The stacks of old books on each table. The color palette. The pop of color with the flowers.⁣
⁣
My point? Classrooms can be just as awesome without being super elaborate. Focus more on it being inclusive for all students 💛⁣
⁣
If you haven't had a chance to check out the Classroom Environment + Design Conference, be sure to click the link in my bio! Our main priority and focus of the conference is sharing ideas about creating a safe, inclusive place. ✨⁣
⁣
You’ll have immediate, lifetime access to the sessions. Tickets are only for sale until July 21, so be sure to grab them now!
